completely after delivery","Sheehan syndrome occurs due to pituitary infarction during severe postpartum haemorrhage","Sheehan syndrome is more common in nulliparous women","Sheehan syndrome primarily affects the posterior pituitary"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELymphocytic hypophysitis\u003C/strong\u003E is an autoimmune condition that predominantly affects women, particularly during late pregnancy or the postpartum period. It does not \u003Cstrong\u003Eoccur only in early first trimester\u003C/strong\u003E and does not typically \u003Cstrong\u003Eresolve completely after delivery\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESheehan syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E occurs when severe postpartum haemorrhage causes hypotension and subsequent pituitary infarction. The enlarged pituitary gland of pregnancy is particularly susceptible to ischaemic damage. It is not more common in \u003Cstrong\u003Enulliparous women\u003C/strong\u003E as it requires pregnancy-related changes to occur.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile \u003Cstrong\u003Eposterior pituitary\u003C/strong\u003E function can be affected, Sheehan syndrome primarily causes anterior pituitary dysfunction, leading to varying degrees of hypopituitarism.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Lymphocytic hypophysitis predominantly affects women during late pregnancy or postpartum period","Sheehan syndrome is postpartum pituitary necrosis due to severe haemorrhage causing hypopituitarism","The pituitary gland enlarges during pregnancy making it more susceptible to ischaemic damage"],"references":["Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine 